27/04/2005
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- UNMIK chief Soren Jessen-Petersen said Tuesday (26 April) that his administration is considering the possibility of organising an international conference that could bring together Serbian President Boris Tadic and his Kosovo counterpart, Ibrahim Rugova. 
According to the top UN official, such a meeting should take place as soon as possible. 
The statement comes amid recent signs from Belgrade that Tadic is ready to meet Rugova for direct talks on Kosovo-related issues. 
(Beta, Tanjug - 26/04/05)
